  "doc_id": "8734",
  "text": ". This is because the former measures are usually questionnaires that can overlook some specific difficulties. Consequently, some individual difficulties may not be included in these questionnaires and therefore important data can be lost. Quantitative assessment of functional deficits can indicate early functional changes that are clinically meaningful. Moreover, this method of assessment can be more sensitive for distinguishing healthy elderly from MCI elderly [CITATION_1] . The Canadian Occupational Performance Measure (COPM) is an instrument that can identify individual difficulties in performing ADL [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] 11 . The COPM is based on the CMOP, a client-centered instrument. It is an individualized measure designed to identify changes in self-perceived occupational performance",
